President Obama has announced his intent to nominate and appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. The nominees for Ambassador positions include Erica J. Barks Ruggles for the Republic of Rwanda, Brent Robert Hartley for the Republic of Slovenia, Donald L. Heflin for the Republic of Cabo Verde, and Earl Robert Miller for the Republic of Botswana. David Pressman has been nominated for the position of Alternate Representative of the United States for Special Political Affairs in the United Nations. Additionally, President Obama intends to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts, including John Anderson and Roger N. Beachy as members of the National Science Board, Vicki Chandler as a member of the National Science Board, Robert M. Groves as a member of the National Science Board, James S. Jackson as a member of the National Science Board, Sethuraman Panchanathan as a member of the National Science Board, Rodney Ewing as Chairman of the Nuclear Waste Technical Review Board, Sue Clark as a member of the Nuclear Waste Technical Review Board, Linda Nozick as a member of the Nuclear Waste Technical Review Board, Kenneth Peddicord as a member of the Nuclear Waste Technical Review Board, and Paul Turinsky as a member of the Nuclear Waste Technical Review Board. President Obama stated that these individuals will bring talent and expertise to their new roles and he looks forward to working with them in the future.